From the respective ends of the political spectrum, they are an insult to the honorific.Out of their unbridled mouths come toxic words and utterances that are not just rude and primitive, but ultimately divide the people and incite hatred and violence. Social media junkies have in the past few days catapulted two video clips of a pair of Kenyan politicians on best behaviour to the top of the trending charts.
Malindi MP Aisha Jumwa and ODM Secretary-General Edwin Sifuna going hammer and tongs at each other in absolutely unbridled fashion clearly excited many Kenyans, who enthusiastically shared and ‘liked’ the videos on WhatsApps and other digital chats platforms.



