Msambweni represents early skirmishes on the supremacy battle around the impending Building Bridges Initiative referendum championed by President Kenyatta and ODM leader Odinga against the ‘No’ forces grouped around Deputy President Ruto.





Barking dogs
And that in itself is just one staging ground ahead of the 2022 General Election where President Kenyatta seems to be assembling a vast effort to block the prospects of his estranged deputy succeeding him in State House.
We can thus presume that in all the verbal garbage, Ms Jumwa, Mr Sifuna and others of their ilk are nothing more than mere mouthpieces at the respective service of Ruto or the Uhuru-Raila duo.
The real principals own the barking dogs, and as long as they are not calling them to heel, own their words as well as any consequences that may arise, including hatred, suspicion and political violence.
Now, before turning our fury on the principal leaders, we must look inward at ourselves. We own them. We are responsible for elevating Mr Kenyatta, Mr Odinga, Mr Ruto and other national leaders to the lofty perches they occupy.
They did not get up there by stealth, subterfuge or violent capture, but by our own free will in abuse of the sacred right to vote.



