We get the leaders we deserve. That applies to the aforementioned fellows at the apex, footsoldiers such as Sifuna and Jumwa, and fellow dishonourables the likes of Mike Sonko, Kimani Ngunjuri, Oscar Sudi, Milly Odhiambo, Sospeter Ojaamong and Purity Ngiricha, et cetera.
They are us and we are them. Whatever they say or do reflects who we are. Uganda, Ethiopia, Somalia and Sudan have been experiencing internal conflicts. Real gangsters reserved raw violence for their direct opposite competitors — the police, he says. US president-elect praises voters for casting ballots in record numbers on November 3.